HEADWORD: Watteau
<hw>Wat*teau"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Art)</fld>
<def>Having the appearance of that which is seen in pictures by
<person>Antoine <etsep>Watteau</etsep></person>, a French painter of the
eighteenth century; -- said esp. of women's garments; <as>as, a
<ex>Watteau</ex> bodice</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

